WEBMASTERS TIP - A Search Engine "Secret"

Note: In code examples I add a period after each left arrow
bracket so the code can be viewed in all email programs. If 
youcopy and paste, be sure to remove the periods or it won't 
work.

Here's one of those so-called search engine secrets: Some 
searchengines will only crawl to two or three levels deep 
on your site. Bycreating a site map which lists every page 
of your site and linking to it from your index page, you en-
sure that even the search engines that limit the depth that 
their spiders crawl will still find all your pages, or, up 
to the maximum number of pages a search engine will index 
from any one domain in some cases.

Here's how a spidering search engine see your site:

Top: Index page
Level One: Site Map (and any page linked-to from your in-
dex page)
Level Two: All your pages, if you have a site map on level 
one.
Level Three: Who Cares! You win!

Hey, I've got another secret for you. Creating a site map, 
even for avery large site, is easy. There's a nifty free-
ware utility called Index Generator that does the work for 
you. See today's Software Spotlight for this gem.

